refentry.refsect1:
    Description

     stringPDOStatement::fetchSingle



     &warn.experimental.func;


      PDOStatement::fetchSingle returns the first column
      in the next row of a result set as a string value.




       There is no way to return the second or subsequent columns from a row
       if you use this method to retrieve data.



     Return first column of the next row


<?php
$sth = $dbh->prepare("SELECT name, colour FROM fruit");
$sth->execute();

/* Fetch the first column from the next row in the result set */
print("Fetch the first column from the next row in the result set:\n");
$result = $sth->fetchSingle();
print("$result\n");

$result = $sth->fetchSingle();
print("$result\n");
?>



     &example.outputs;


Fetch the first column from the next row in the result set:
lemon
orange
